---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Jeff Melton - DevOps & Platform Engineering Consultant">
    <style>
        /* Custom gradient for hero section */
        .hero-gradient {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
        }

    </style>

    <section class="hero-gradient text-white py-16 text-center" id="home">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">DevOps & Platform Engineering Consultant</h1>
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl mb-8 opacity-90 max-w-4xl mx-auto">I work across the entire problem-solving lifecycle‚Äîfrom identifying systemic issues that span multiple domains, to designing comprehensive solutions that address root causes, to building and implementing the technical platforms that make those solutions sustainable.</p>
            <a href="#case-studies" class="inline-block bg-red-500 hover:bg-red-600 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-lg">See My Work</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" id="what-i-do">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-slate-700">What I Do</h2>
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
                <p class="text-lg mb-6 px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">I specialize in diagnosing and solving technical problems that require both deep systems expertise and business context understanding. My work typically involves complex, multi-domain challenges where technical solutions must align with organizational realities and business objectives.</p>
                
                <p class="text-lg mb-6 px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">Whether it's infrastructure that's constraining business growth, systems that don't integrate properly across departments, or operational processes that waste engineering resources‚ÄîI work from problem identification through solution design to technical implementation. I don't just identify what's broken; I understand why it matters to the business and build sustainable platforms that prevent similar problems from recurring.</p>

                <p class="text-lg mb-6 px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">My approach combines technical depth with organizational insight, ensuring that solutions are not only technically sound but operationally viable and strategically aligned with business needs.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" id="tools">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-slate-700">Tools & Platform Engineering</h2>
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center mb-12">
                <p class="text-lg px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">I build comprehensive tooling platforms that transform operational friction into automated excellence. Rather than accepting enterprise constraints as unchangeable, I engineer solutions that work within real-world limitations while dramatically improving productivity and reliability. <a href="/tools" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-600 font-semibold transition-colors">View Full Platform ‚Üí</a></p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-center mb-4"><a href="/tools" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">üè• Fleet Health Monitoring</a></h3>
                    <p class="text-base"><strong>Challenge:</strong> Manual cluster validation across 6000+ Kubernetes clusters took 5-10 days.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Elixir-based concurrent health monitoring system.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> 99.9% time reduction (days to 8-12 minutes), 2000+ engineering hours saved annually.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-center mb-4"><a href="/tools" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">üéØ Operations Automation</a></h3>
                    <p class="text-base"><strong>Challenge:</strong> Daily operations required extensive context switching across multiple enterprise systems.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Unified dashboard and automation tools (Rust/Go) integrating Kubernetes, vSphere, ServiceNow, and monitoring systems.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> 2-3 hours saved daily, 75% reduction in incident response time.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-center mb-4"><a href="/tools" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">üöÄ Infrastructure Management</a></h3>
                    <p class="text-base"><strong>Challenge:</strong> Complex GPU and VM lifecycle management across hybrid infrastructure required manual coordination.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Intelligent automation with cross-system correlation and safety validation.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> $400K+ operational overhead reduction, eliminated manual errors.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="text-center mt-8 p-8 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-4">Platform Philosophy</h3>
                <p class="italic text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg">
                    "Enterprise friction should be solved through engineering, not accepted as unchangeable constraint. Each tool represents a decision to automate rather than tolerate, integrate rather than context-switch, and optimize rather than accept suboptimal workflows."
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gray-50" id="case-studies">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-slate-700">Case Studies</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-center mb-4"><a href="/case-studies/legacy-infrastructure-modernization" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">Legacy Infrastructure Modernization</a></h3>
                    <p class="text-base"><strong>Challenge:</strong> InfoSec-mandated SLES 11 EOL upgrade across Fortune One retailer's 600+ locations while maintaining existing hardware to maximize asset depreciation.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> 18-month platform engineering transformation balancing compliance requirements with business constraints, building comprehensive operational capabilities.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> $2M+ cost avoidance, 150:1 location-to-engineer efficiency, zero-downtime migrations with sustainable Day One operations.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-center mb-4"><a href="/case-studies/platform-engineering" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">Platform Engineering at Scale</a></h3>
                    <p class="text-base"><strong>Challenge:</strong> 6000+ Kubernetes cluster infrastructure with 5-10 day manual validation cycles costing ~$40M annually in downtime risk.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Engineered concurrent monitoring platform and integrated operations toolkit using Elixir, Rust, and Go.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> $400K+ cost avoidance, 99.9% time reduction (days to minutes), 2000+ engineering hours reclaimed annually.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-center mb-4"><a href="/case-studies/strategic-architecture" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">Strategic Architecture & Enterprise Decision Dynamics</a></h3>
                    <p class="text-base"><strong>Challenge:</strong> Design next-generation infrastructure for 600+ locations balancing VMware contract renewal, emerging AI/ML requirements, and enterprise CapEx constraints.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Comprehensive architecture evaluation, vendor management, and financial analysis presenting optimal solutions while respecting business decision-making autonomy.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> Strategic foresight validated by subsequent organizational planning, demonstrating sophisticated enterprise consulting approach.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" id="approach">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-slate-700">My Approach</h2>
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
                <p class="text-lg mb-6 px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">Every organization is different, but the patterns of technical debt and systemic dysfunction are remarkably consistent. I start by understanding not just what's broken, but why it broke ‚Äì what organizational or technical constraints led to the current state.</p>
                
                <p class="text-lg mb-6 px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">Then I design solutions that work within your actual constraints, not theoretical ideal conditions. This often means building tools and processes that route around organizational limitations while gradually addressing root causes.</p>
                
                <p class="text-lg mb-6 px-4 sm:px-8 text-left">The goal isn't just to solve the immediate problem, but to leave you with better systems, clearer processes, and the tools to prevent similar issues in the future.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>